The paper describes a set of natural language processing tools for Danish, which suggests that it belongs to the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The tools are machine-learning based, indicating that it may also belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of natural language processing models, which could place it in the sub-category of information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of cybernetics (cs.CY), which deals with the study of communication and control in the animal and machine.
